{{Quote|The Battle of Mizra (1466 B.B.Y.) saw the victory of a massive Sith army over the Jedi. It was immortalized by the poet Felloux, who described scores of Sith speeders bearing scores of Sith Lords ''[&hellip;]|''The New Essential Chronology''|<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref>}}
'''Felloux''' was a [[Poet/Legends|poet]] who composed a [[Felloux's work|work]] detailing the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] victory at the [[Battle of Mizra]], a battle which took place in [[1466 BBY]] as part of the [[New Sith Wars]]. The piece detailed the vast number of [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lords]] plummeting from a [[Atmosphere/Legends|sky]] thick with ash. Felloux noted that each rode a [[Speeder/Legends|speeder]] named for a predatory animal that represented their individual personalities, and that the noise produced by the sheer number of [[Repulsorlift/Legends|repulsorlift]] vehicles drowned out the screams of those [[Death/Legends|dying]] in the conflict. [[The New Essential Chronology (in-universe)|''The New Essential Chronology'']]&mdash;a book published by the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic's]] [[Historical Council]] under the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances]]&mdash;was published in [[36 ABY]] and detailed aspects of Felloux's piece describing the Battle of Mizra.<ref name="NEC" />

==Behind the scenes==
Felloux was mentioned in the [[2005]] reference book ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'', which was written by [[Daniel Wallace]].<ref name="NEC" />

